DESCRIPTION:She's peopled her last please\, now she's figuring out hey ‘w
 hy can’t she be desired’? Why can’t she be naughty? Why can’t she b
 e made out of HDPE plastic? Her exterior’s hard plastic but inside she's 
 stagnant air from 1991. Bex can’t hide behind a toy kitchen mask anymore.
 .. she's 5ft8. A fragile woman made entity! Whose masquerading as someone w
 hose normal. But not really. Instead of sharp edges Bex has soft curves\, a
  sturdy base and a small rack. Who is she but a toy kitchen? Join whimsical
  and (sometimes scary) comedian Bex Turner for a (mostly) stand-up show of 
 weird tales\, Autism and lots of crude Crudités! Bex Turner is a high ener
 gy\, eccentric\, surreal\, stand up/character comic. Her likeability combin
 ed with her comedic sense of adventure makes audiences love her. She was a 
 2018 Quarter Finalist at Leicester Square New Comedian of the Year and a 20
 15 Semi Finalist for Laughing Horse New Act of the Year.\nMore info: https:
 //comedyatlas.app/comedy-atlas/event/mommas-got-a-brand-new-toy-kitchen/
